./Theocracy#cite_ref-5" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-5" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt12" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://www.gutenberg.org/files/2849/2849-h/2849-h.htm"},"title":{"wt":"Against Apion by Flavius Josephus,  Book II, Chapter 17"},"work":{"wt":"gutenberg.org"},"date":{"wt":"October 2001"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAWM"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.gutenberg.org/files/2849/2849-h/2849-h.htm" id="mwAWQ"><i id="mwAWU">Against Apion by Flavius Josephus,  Book II, Chapter 17</i></a>. <i id="mwAWY">gutenberg.org</i>. October 2001.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Against+Apion+by+Flavius+Josephus%2C++Book+II%2C+Chapter+17&amp;rft.date=2001-10&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gutenberg.org%2Ffiles%2F2849%2F2849-h%2F2849-h.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATheocracy" class="Z3988" about="#mwt12" id="mwAWc"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt12" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAWg"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-6" id="cite_note-6"><a href="./Theocracy#cite_ref-6" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-6" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/14568a.htm" id="mwAWk">Catholic Encyclopedia</a> "A form of civil government in which God himself is recognized as the head."</span></li><li about="#cite_note-7" id="cite_note-7"><a href="./Theocracy#cite_ref-7" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-7" class="mw-reference-text">English form the 17th century (<i id="mwAWo"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./OED" title="OED" id="mwAWs" class="mw-redirect">OED</a></i>).
The Greek term is explicitly coined by Josephus and isn't attested elsewhere in Ancient Greek; Josephus marks it as a <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Nonce_word" title="Nonce word" id="mwAWw">nonce</a> coinage by calling it a "strained expression".
W. Whiston tr. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Josephus" title="Josephus" id="mwAW0">Josephus</a>, <i id="mwAW4">Against Apion</i> ii. §17 (1814) IV. 340: "He [Moses] ordained our government to be what, by a strained expression, may be termed a Theocracy", translating  <span lang="grc" title="Ancient Greek language text" about="#mwt23" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"lang","href":"./Template:Lang"},"params":{"1":{"wt":"grc"},"2":{"wt":"ὡς δ&apos;ἄν τίς εἴποι, βιασάμενος τὸν λόγον, θεοκρατίαν"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAW8">ὡς δ'ἄν τίς εἴποι, βιασάμενος τὸν λόγον, θεοκρατίαν</span><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Articles_containing_Ancient_Greek-language_text" about="#mwt23" id="mwAXA"/>
</span></li><li about="#cite_note-8" id="cite_note-8"><a href="./Theocracy#cite_ref-8" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-8" class="mw-reference-text">Stephen Palmquist, <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.hkbu.edu.hk/~ppp/bth" id="mwAXE"><i id="mwAXI">Biblical Theocracy: A vision of the biblical foundations for a Christian political philosophy</i></a> (Hong Kong: Philopsychy Press, 1993), introduced these more precise uses of the terms in arguing that theocracy (in this pure sense) is the only political system defended in the Bible. While Palmquist defends theocracy in this pure form as a viable (though "non-political") political system, he warns that what normally goes by this name is actually ecclesiocracy, the most dangerous of all political systems.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-9" id="cite_note-9"><a href="./Theocracy#cite_ref-9" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-9" class="mw-reference-text">Akyol, Mustafa. <i id="mwAXM">Islam without extremes</i> W.W.Norton, 2013, p. 56</span></li><li about="#cite_note-10" id="cite_note-10"><a href="./Theocracy#cite_ref-10" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-10" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation journal" about="#mwt32" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite journal","href":"./Template:Cite_journal"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Vitalone"},"first1":{"wt":"Alessia"},"title":{"wt":"Il Pontefice sovrano dello Stato della Città del Vaticano"},"date":{"wt":"2007"},"page":{"wt":"313"},"journal":{"wt":"Diritto e Religioni"},"volume":{"wt":"II"},"issue":{"wt":"1"},"url":{"wt":"https://books.google.com/?id=MS7YXQDBHGWBHU0C&amp;pg=PA313&amp;lpg=PA313&amp;dq=%22citt%C3%A0+del+vaticano%22+%22stato+della+chiesa%22+continuit%C3%A0#v=onepage&amp;q=%22citt%C3%A0%20del%20vaticano%22%20%22stato%20della%20chiesa%22%20continuit%C3%A0&amp;f=false"},"accessdate":{"wt":"20 March 2015"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwAXQ">Vitalone, Alessia (2007). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/?id=MS7YXQDBHGWBHU0C&amp;pg=PA313&amp;lpg=PA313&amp;dq=%22citt%C3%A0+del+vaticano%22+%22stato+della+chiesa%22+continuit%C3%A0#v=onepage&amp;q=%22citt%C3%A0%20del%20vaticano%22%20%22stato%20della%20chiesa%22%20continuit%C3%A0&amp;f=false" id="mwAXU">"Il Pontefice sovrano dello Stato della Città del Vaticano"</a>. <i id="mwAXY">Diritto e Religioni</i>. <b id="mwAXc">II</b> (1): 313<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwAXg">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwAXk">20 March</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Diritto+e+Religioni&amp;rft.atitle=Il+Pontefice+sovrano+dello+Stato+della+Citt%C3%A0+del+Vaticano&amp;rft.volume=II&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.pages=313&amp;rft.date=2007&amp;rft.aulast=Vitalone&amp;rft.aufirst=Alessia&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2F%3Fid%3DMS7YXQDBHGWBHU0C%26pg%3DPA313%26lpg%3DPA313%26dq%3D%2522citt%25C3%25A0%2Bdel%2Bvaticano%2522%2B%2522stato%2Bdella%2Bchiesa%2522%2Bcontinuit%25C3%25A0%23v%3Donepage%26q%3D%2522citt%25C3%25A0%2520del%2520vaticano%2522%2520%2522stato%2520della%2520chiesa%2522%2520continuit%25C3%25A0%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATheocracy" class="Z3988" about="#mwt32" id="mwAXo"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt32" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwAXs"/><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:All_articles_with_dead_external_links" about="#mwt33" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"Dead link","href":"./Template:Dead_